<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="A-hungry" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">A-hungry,</orth> for hungry, used by Slender, <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.280" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 280</bibl>, and Sir Andrew, <bibl n="shak. tn 2.3.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 3, 136</bibl>; Marcius even says <cit><quote>an hungry,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 209</bibl></cit>, in imitation of the populace. But cf. St. <bibl n="Mark2.25" default="NO">Mark II, 25</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>